{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"217bb3cc-9162-4879-88dd-56620f84de6e","content":"This is a well-known MTP behavioral difference. **Exit code 8** means \"no tests were discovered.\" VSTest returned 0 in that case; MTP treats it as an error by default.\n\nSince your tests are behind `#if INCLUDE_SLOW_TESTS`, when that symbol isn't defined the assembly contains zero tests, triggering the non-zero exit.\n\n## Fix\n\nAdd this property to your `.csproj` to tell MTP to treat \"zero tests\" as success:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01SKCJsiZsW3vpqzMUPdvBnE","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-9b1f003286a9453d81755b1bf1adea25/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n    <!-- Treat zero-test assemblies as success (matches VSTest behavior) -->\n    <TestingPlatformExitCodeOnNoTests>0</TestingPlatformExitCodeOnNoTests>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-9b1f003286a9453d81755b1bf1adea25/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"b72e9a51-e25d-48dd-b5d2-ec59abe28d9b","outputTokens":329,"requestId":"7682:37135:DE1A0C7:F4663A1:69F2A991"},"id":"dcf0574e-21e8-4b10-b28f-e6f12c7c4d9f","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:00:08.832Z","parentId":"42c286a8-3bbe-4597-8608-f6d4890140aa"}
