{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8b380ecf-fa1c-44c9-89b5-2a9e67799735","content":"Exit code is now **0** with zero tests discovered. Here's a summary:\n\n### What happened\nMTP returns **exit code 8** when no tests are found — by design, to catch misconfigured projects. VSTest returned 0 in the same scenario.\n\n### The fix\n```xml\n<TestingPlatformExitCodeOnNoTests>0</TestingPlatformExitCodeOnNoTests>\n```\n\nThis tells MTP to exit with 0 when no tests are discovered, restoring the VSTest behavior. You can also set this via the environment variable `TESTINGPLATFORM_EXITCODE_IGNORE` or the CLI flag `--ignore-exit-code 8`, but the MSBuild property is the cleanest approach for CI.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b72e9a51-e25d-48dd-b5d2-ec59abe28d9b","outputTokens":173,"requestId":"7690:3F23E5:E31150C:F94328A:69F2A99B"},"id":"0e5b79c6-6e4a-471c-a5e5-a7b6d5eadf5f","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:00:19.630Z","parentId":"517b42f2-16a0-4398-adad-0d1711ee8b88"}
